cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB. 

The paper addresses the problem of cross-referencing short texts with Wikipedia pages, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new system, TAGME, which uses machine learning and knowledge representation techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the efficiency and effectiveness of the annotation process, which involves optimization and evaluation techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DB (Databases) possible sub-categories.
